# Legacy Shopify blog URLs. Articles now live as static HTML at /blog/[slug].
# Earlier these went through a JS-redirect shim at /blog/post.html, but Google
# was splitting equity across 3+ URL variants per article (see GSC report
# 2026-05-25). Send each legacy URL directly to its canonical static page in
# one hop.
/blogs/blogs-maple-terroir       /blog/         301
/blogs/blogs-maple-terroir/*     /blog/:splat   301
/blogs/news                      /blog/         301
/blogs/news/*                    /blog/:splat   301

# Renamed: numeric Shopify slug -> keyword-rich URL. Keep this 301 so the indexed
# /blog/1123 does not 404.
/blog/1123  /blog/maple-syrup-extraction-optimization-sustainable-agriculture  301

# Retire the old dynamic blog template. There is NO functions/_middleware.js on this
# project (it is a Worker with Static Assets; Pages Functions never run), so these two
# variants were silently 404ing and bleeding link equity (GSC: equity split across
# /blog/post.html?, /blog/post?, and /blogs/blogs-maple-terroir/ per article).
# _redirects CANNOT read the ?handle= query param (Cloudflare does not support query
# matching in _redirects), so it can only send these to the blog hub as a floor that
# stops the 404. Per-article precision (handle -> /blog/<handle>) is a Cloudflare
# Single Redirect Rule in the dashboard, which runs at the edge BEFORE _redirects and
# wins when a handle is present. See CLAUDE.md "DNS and domain redirects".
/blog/post.html  /blog/  301
/blog/post       /blog/  301

